news.title: House prices dip marginally in UK in August 2024
news.para: In annual terms, prices were 2.4% higher than in August last year, the fastest increase since December 2022 - shortly after the "mini-budget" crisis that pushed up borrowing costs - but a smaller gain than the median forecast of 2.9% in the poll.

news.title: WeWork India in talks to lease 400,000 sq ft in Delhi, Gurugram
news.para: The company is taking 148,000 at Prestige Trade Tower and 115,000 at Bharti Worldmark 6 at Delhi’s Aerocity, besides 140,000 at DLF’sCyber City in Gurgaon.

news.title: China's Kaisa posts 36.3% increase in losses in H1 2024
news.para: Chinese property developer Kaisa posted on Thursday a 36.3 percent increase in losses, highlighting the persistent challenges faced by real estate firms as home sales decline in a slowing economy. Losses increased by 36.3 percent compared to the same period last year, when it totalled 6.6 billion yuan ($930 million).

news.title: Goa: Construction permissions continue to be granted based on earlier ODPs & RP 2021
news.para: TCP chief town planner Rajesh Naik said that in the absence of any applicable statutory provisions, the same ODP or development plan which was in force in “affected planning areas” on the date of its withdrawal shall continue to apply.

news.title: Formulate plans to make Amaravati into AI city: Andhra Pradesh CM
news.para: Andhra Pradesh Chief Minister N Chandrababu Naidu has directed officials to develop Amaravati into an Artificial Intelligence city. He emphasized the swift completion of government buildings and revival of the HappyNest project. Naidu also called for the speedy implementation of Metro rail projects in Vijayawada and Visakhapatnam.

news.title: Hosur metro extension faces final hurdles
news.para: The study, conducted by Balaji Rail Road Systems, is nearly complete. CMRL has sought the assistance of BMRCL to finalise the report.

news.title: Ulhasnagar civic body to demolish 16-floor illegal building
news.para: This includes a 120-foot DP road on the front side and an 80-foot DP road on the other side. In such a situation, although UMC has asked the developer to demolish the illegal portion of the building, technically, the entire structure will have to be demolished.

news.title: Kolkata civic body set to amend law to deal with illegal buildings
news.para: A stricter law, said a KMC buildings department official, would help the civic body prosecute and jail unscrupulous builders for a longer time for not only going ahead with constructions without seeking civic sanction but also using inferior materials, endangering public safety.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body, GMC to get infra cess share directly into accounts
news.para: Infrastructure cess — a 2% charge collected as a part of stamp duty on the sale and purchase of new property — is collected by the state govt and released to ULBs and development authorities in instalments.

news.title: SC nod for purchasable FAR, to allow 13,000 more Amrapali flats to come up
news.para: All parties, including Noida and Greater Noida authorities, NBCC, and homebuyers, have agreed to the purchasable floor area ratio, aiding the completion of pending projects and repayment of debts.

news.title: Construction of Dharavi redevelopment to start in 6-8 months: SVR Srinivas, CEO, DRP
news.para: The Dharavi Redevelopment Project, covering nearly 600 acres in Mumbai, will start in 6-8 months. A survey for eligibility will end by March. Adani Group and the Government of Maharashtra lead the project. It's a joint venture poised to rehabilitate residents of Dharavi, aiming to reimagine one of the largest informal settlements.

news.title: Noida DM tells builders to clear dues and expedite registry of flats
news.para: From Feb 26 to Aug 29, 2024, a total of 7,368 flats were registered in GB Nagar. Of these, 5,297 flats were registered under rehabilitation schemes, while the remaining 2,070 flats were registered through the routine process.

news.title: Maharashtra government to consider stamp duty concession on property registration
news.para: Atul Save, Minister of Housing, Government of Maharashtra, said it would consider the real estate developers' demand of granting further concessions in registration and stamp duty.

news.title: Macrotech Developers acquires Opexefi Services & One Box Warehouse for Rs 95.76 crore
news.para: While Opexefi Services has been acquired for Rs 46.67 crore, One Box Warehouse has been acquired for Rs 49.09 crore.

news.title: Trehan IRIS to manage Marriott International's hotel in Greater Noida
news.para: In 2022, Trehan IRIS had announced an investment of around Rs 400 crore to develop this commercial project, comprising retail and office spaces as well as a hotel, in Greater Noida.

news.title: Betting on Chinese demand, Hong Kong developers turn to rental market
news.para: Rents of private homes in Hong Kong in July rose to their highest level in nearly five years, while home prices dropped 22% during the same period, latest data showed on Wednesday.

news.title: Industry came forward for regulations on small & medium REITs: Sebi chief
news.para: Recently Sebi implemented regulations for small and medium real estate investment trusts (SM REITs) aimed at significantly increasing investor interest in fractional ownership of real estate assets.
